metadata.description:
There's always an internal struggle between walking on the beaten path or off of it. And that comes from the illusion that the choice is really a thing. Although we are slaves of our internal processes, we shall never be the slaves of others.

metadata.name: Layers #51
metadata.description:
It's the first time I really delved into studying about P5JS

I spent the last one collecting generative art and it made my passion for all this just grow, as a collector I wanted to move forward and want to do something more and so developed this project. 

I've been a designer for almost 10 years, an art director for over 1 year, I work all day with design every day, Photoshop and its infinite layers haunt me all day, as my passion wanted to insert something related there in my work so I thought of "layers" and thus "Layers" was born, layers and layers, specifically of rectangles one on top of the other forming the interactions of this work.

5 Styles:

Dunes:
Curves, some sharp and others less so, some remind me of sand dunes.

moiree:
It reminds me a little of compositions with a MoirÃ© effect, forming curves where there is the presence of shadows giving relief.

Arranged:

A style where there is a certain organization of lines, but not perfect.

Strips:

Strips of colors on top of each other.

Harmonic:
It forms flat compositions, they are more organized layers.


17 Color Palettes based on famous works such as paintings and compositions:

"Mondrian - Composition with Large Red Plane, Yellow, Black, Gray and Blue / Piet Mondrian"
"Monalisa - Leonardo da Vinci"
"Portrait - Van Gogh self-portrait / Van Gogh"
"Venus - The Birth of Venus / Sandro Botticelli"
"Memory - The Persistence of Memory / Salvador DalÃ­"
"Son - The Son of Man /RenÃ© Magritte"
"Guitarist - The Old Guitarist / Pablo Picasso"
"Canna - Red Canna / Georgia O'Keeffe"
"Drowning - Drowning Girl / Roy Lichtenstein"
"American - American Gothic / Grant Wood"
"Sunrise - Impression, Sunrise / Claude Monet"
"Creation - The Creation of Adam / Michelangelo"
"Girl - Girl with a Pearl Earring / Johannes Vermeer"
"Square - Black Square / Kazimir Malevich"
"Wave - The Great Wave off Kanagawa / Katsushika Hokusai"
"Wanderer - Wanderer above the Sea of â€‹â€‹Fog / David Friedrich"
"Scream - The Scream / Edvard Munch"

"Layers" uses grains/noises function by Gorilla Sun, thanks for sharing your article with us! Article https://www.fxhash.xyz/article/all-about-that-grain

Created with p5js / Alex Benedith

metadata.name: CHIP #150
metadata.description:
A CHIP is being constructed by using two brushes that are painting on the board through deterministic noise, and then turned squared and pixelated and blended into each other, with colours selected from 21 different colour schemes. How many iterations, and the speed and size of the added parts determines the final composition. 

You can stop the iterations by pressing S, and download the current composition by hitting D, and restart/reload the iterations by pressing R.

Notes
The thumbnail generation takes a while and the render/iterations in non-GPU browser can be quite slow. Chrome/Firefox recommended.

I could go on describing the details of this piece but honestly I just wanted to create something very colorful for the party, without putting too many hidden meanings! :)
(Or maybe not...)

Happy birthday fxhash!

80% of primary sales will be donated to the Processing Foundation and Save Pakistan.

The texture might look weird in thumbnails, so I recommend opening the piece in full screen and/or download the png by pressing "s".

metadata.name: THE CONSTRUCTIONS #38
metadata.description:
This application code is built using ThreeJs, it render 3D to SVG. Since I created the first handmade version of these compositions in May 2022, I have been working on this generative version, which is now complete. The fxrandom function is executed 380-780 times, which affects the number, size, color, transparency and animation of the elements, so that each generated creation is completely unique.

After generation, the animation starts: first the elements come in, and then it shows the two side views, during which it switches to split screen and then returns to the original view. You can interrupt this animation at any time by interacting with the mouse or keyboard shortcuts:

- You can rotate the object with the mouse move (touch on mobile).
- You can change view with the arrows to 4 preset.

<- Left - side view
-> Right - another side view
â†‘ Up - top view
â†“ Down - default view

- Spacebar switch to split screen or back
- "d" - restart animation
- "s" - save an svg from current view

Theo Van Doesburg inspired this work, itâ€™s also a tribute to his oeuvre.

Theo van Doesburg was a Dutch artist, who practiced painting, writing, poetry and architecture. He is best known as the founder and leader of De Stijl. He developed a greater interest in architecture in the early 1920s and even abandoned painting for a time in order to devote himself to investigating architectural and spatial problems.

He met Cornelis van Eesteren with whom he collaborated on a series of projects that were shown at the Galerie Lâ€™Effort Moderne in Paris in 1923. The models and axonometric projections he and Van Eesteren made for the exhibition, in which they studied the distinction between the two-dimensionality of painting and the three-dimensionality of architecture, and his own architectural constructions in primary colours, in which the interior and exterior were interrelated, are reflected in the Construction in Space-Time series.

100 years later

This type of the new media art is interactive for the viewer can view the composition from a different point. Van Doesburg has outgrown his age with his works. 100 years later his works regains its relevance by extend this experience into 3-dimensional space displayed by computers.

Have fun and build! :)
